{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12211: Attribute text on a html tag overrides inner content",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:00.897263+00:00",
  "text": "Attribute text on a html tag overrides inner content\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.12\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/vitejs-vite-v477mx?file=src%2FApp.vue\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nAdd to html tag a attribute **text**\n\n### What is expected?\n\nattribute text does not override content html tag a\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nattribute text overrides content html tag a\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
